column5: Was out on Simcoe yesterday and stumbled across this guy. Never seen one before.
Beautiful bird and great picture & like you I've never seen one in the wild either.
Hard to clean and not good eating. Â Did you catch any fish?
Lots and lots of them around
Been a few robins here all winter but this morning I heard my first Red Wing Blackbird and a few Grackles are back too
nice...probably come to snack on minnow fragments scattered over the ice
Saw my first bald eagle of the year this morning circling over the farm
Great pic - see a few each winter, but I've never seen one on the lake
